Happy to hear you are a Beninese living in the Benin Republic. Benin citizens should always be comfortable in their own countries, for which reason I undertake to start by evaluating your problem. The pension system in Benin is intended to favour persons who, at retirement, will have accumulated 120 months of contributions, and who meet other requirements set by the law. However, to know all of these requirements, it is necessary to purchase the regulations of the pension and to consult them carefully. Regarding the support for the setting up of pension, therefore, try to consult the regulations of the pension and find a knowledgeable person to help you fill in the form.

To read the pensions regulations of the Benin, you can:

1.- Visit the French pension website of the country:

https://www.pref-etatcivil.agir.gouv.fr/carte-didentite-passeport-pereegal-benin

2.- Call the number 114 of your country phone (free). Since GSM lines are not allowed at the time of recording, call a private operator number to place the recording.

Attention !!!

To listen to the French pension rules, you can allocate 15 minutes hautovox on this French phone number whose the access code is 144.
